    theorem.  (i.e.  D=SQRT((Y1-Y0)*(Y1-Y0)+(X1-X0)*(X1-X0)).
         Each use of the warp engines uses up  some  stardates  and  some
    energy.    If   the   Enterprise  is  blocked  by  an  object  during
    intra-quadrant travel, it will stop in front of  the  object.   Using
    the  other  devices  also  results in the loss of some stardates (see
    list of commands) but not as much as for the warp engines.
         Klingons in a quadrant may fire at the Enterprise as  it  begins
    to move and as it comes to a stop.
         A space warp may throw the enterprise off  course  while  moving
    between quadrants.
         Impulse drive will be automatically used (Maxium speed  of  warp
    .3) if the warp drives are damaged.
         A space storm may damage any of the Enterprise's  devices  while
    moving between quadrants.

    Short Range Sensors:

         The short range sensors of the  Enterprise  display  a  detailed
    view  of  the  quadrant  that the Enterprise currently occupies.  The
    Enterprise looks like "E" on the  screen.   Klingon  Battle  Cruisers
    look  like  "K"  on  the screen.  Starbaes look like "B".  stars look
    like "*" and the Klingon Flagship looks like "F".

    Status Report:

         The status report (Generated by  the  battle  computer)  of  the
    Enterprise will list the current stardate, the condition (Red, Amber,
    or Green), the current quadrant, the current sector,  the  amount  of
    energy  units left, the number of photon torpedoes, Klingons, scanner
    probes, and stardates left, and the amount of  deflector  power  left
    (If any).

    Long Range Sensors:

         The long range sensors of the Enterprise display the  number  of
    objects  in the current and surrounding quadrants.  Each digit of the
    number in each box means something:
              The ones digit represents the number of stars.
              The tens digit repesents the number of starbases.
              The hundreds digit represents the number of klingons.
    For Example:
              317 Means 3 Klingons, 1 Starbase, and 7 Stars.
              206 Means 2 Klingons, 0 Starbases, and 6 stars.
              7 Means 0 Klingons, 0 Starbases, and 7 Stars.

         Both short and long range sensors and the status report  may  be
    operated  in the automatic or manual mode.  When in automatic mode, a
    sensor scan will be performed automatically after  each  use  of  the
    warp  engines.  In manual mode, the sensor scan will not be performed
    unless specifically requested.  When both sensors are  in  automactic
    mode, the player must choose which will be first.











