    Phasers:

         Phasers are controlled by the Enterprise Battle  Computer.   The
    computer  automatically  aims  and  fires  the  phasers, dividing the
    allocated energy among the Klingon Cruisers in the quadrant  so  that
    each  Klingon will recieve approximately the same damage.  The energy
    allocated to the phasers will be removed from  the  available  energy
    stores  of  the  Enterprise.   The  Enterprise  is destroyed when its
    available energy goes below zero.  The effectiveness of a hit on  the
    Enterprise  depends  mostly  on the distance from the Klingon and the
    energy available to the Klingon.  A  Klingon  Battle  Cruiser  starts
    with  200 units of energy.  It can repeatedly fire an amount equal to
    what it has left.  If there are more than 4 Klingons one will be  the
    Klingon  Flagship  which  starts the game with 400 energy units.  The
    Enterprise starts the game with its maximum  energy  of  4000  units.
    The  battle  computer will fire phasers only at those Klingons in the
    quadrant which are in the open.  Klingon phasers can do damage to the
    Enterprise's devices if the deflectors are not up.  


         Photon Torpedoes: The  Enterprise  initially  carries  its  full
    complement  of  10  photon  torpedoes.  One hit with a photon torpedo
    will destroy a Klingon or a starbase (Try not  to  destroy  your  own
    starbases).   Two  hits  will  destroy a star.  The range of a photon
    torpedo (Like phasers) is  limited  to  the  current  quadrant.   The
    course  of  a  photon  torpedo  is  set  the  same way as that of the
    Enterprise.

    Damage Control Report:

         The damage control report lists all damaged  devices  and  their
    state  of  repair.   A  negative state of repair indicates a disabled
    device.  Devices can be damaged or repaired by a  space  storm  or  a
    truce,  respectively.   Damage  values  are  decreased or repaired by
    space storm or a truce, respectively.  Damage values are increased by
    one  (Partially  repaired)  each  time  the  warp  drives  are  used.
    Whenever the Enterprise docks at a starbase, the starbase causes  all
    damage  values to be increased by an additional unit.  In addition, a
    truce will cause damaged values to be increased by 1 to 6  additional
    units.

    Deflectors:

         Energy from the Enterprise's enregy stores may be  allocated  to
    the  deflectors.   The  defensive  capabilities  of the deflectors is
    equal to twice the power given them,  but  may  be  used  only  as  a
    protection  against  Klingon attacks.  If the delectors are destroyed
    (Reach zero energy due to a Klingon hit), the enterprise will  suffer
    an  additional  500  unit  energy loss from its energy stores.  Also,
    deflector power returns to 0  when  the  current  quadrant  is  left.
    Lowering  deflector power will cause 25% of the energy in the shields
    to be returned to the energy stores.
    Note: Klingon hits on the Enterprise will reduce the energy stores by









