    an  amount  equal to the hit if deflectors are not activated (Or have
    been destroyed).  The deflectors have a maximum  energy  capacity  of
    4000  energy units.  While deflictors are up the Enterprise's devices
    are protected from damage.

    Communications:

         The  enterprise  may   attempt   to   call   a   truce   through
    communications.   If  the Klingons in the quadrant are badly damaged,
    they may accept.  If the truce is accepted, emergency repairs will be
    effected,  bumping  all  damaged  values from 1 to 6 units.  Also any
    Klingons still alive in the quadrant will be refueled to  their  full
    strength of 200 energy units (Or 400 for the Flagship).

    Starbases:

         You have at least one  supporting  starbase.   As  long  as  the
    Enterprise  is  docked  at  a base (Is positioned next to one), it is
    resupplied with energy and photon torpedoes.

    Transporter:

         The Enterprise can transport photon torpedoes from the  starbase
    in  the present quadrant.  Enough torpedoes will be sent to bring the
    ship's supply up to 10, but some may be lost during  transport.   The
    transporter  will  function only if deflectors are down and the short
    range sensors are operative.

    Shuttlecraft Galileo and Tractor Beam:

         The Enterprise shuttlecraft, the Galileo, begins in  free  space
    somewhere  in  the  galaxy.   It  will  survive  unassisted  for  ten
    stardates.  It does not appear on the sensor scans due to  its  small
    size,  but  it  does send out powerful one-quadrant distress-signals.
    It may be brought aboard the Enterprise by tractor beams, after which
    the Enterprise may use the Galileo sensors which are limited to short
    range scanning and are only partly accurate.  

    Torpedo Spread:

         This command fires from 1 to 8 photon  torpedoes  at  45  degree
    intervals beginning the course specified by the player and continuing
    in a clockwise direction.  The number of torpedoes  to  be  fired  is
    specified by the player.

    Super Long Range Sensor Probes:

         The Enterprise carries a  number  of  super  long  range  sensor
    probes which may be used to gather information about unknown portions
    of the galaxy.  Once a probe has been launched, it travels  until  it
    reaches a quadrant on the edge of the galaxy.  As it passes through a
    quadrant it reports the  number  of  "objects"  that  it  finds.   An
    "object"  is defined as either a Klingon or a starbase.  Starbases do









