    Priority 1 Distress Signal -- 'Colony under attack' The ship computer
    immediately  lays  in  and executes a course to the colony from which
    the signal originated.  No commands may be given.

    Priority 2 Distress Signal -- 'Attack imminent' The course  is  again
    laid  in  immediately,  but  one command may be given before the warp
    engines are used.

    Priority 3 Distress Signal --  'Situation  extremely  dangerous'  The
    course  is  not implemented unless the warp engines would normally be
    used (A command 0 is given) and may be  explicitly  canceled  through
    the use of command 20.

         If the Enterprise's energy stores are insufficient  to  honor  a
    priority 1 or priority 2 distress signal, the distress signal will be
    cancelled.

    Klingon Cloaking Device:

         Due to their recent treaty with the Romulans, the  Klingons  may
    occasionally use a modification of the Romulan cloaking device.  They
    will be effective in battle even if the device is on, and will appear
    only  on  the  initial short range scan of a quadrant and on all long
    range scans.  

    The Effect Of Stars On Weaponry And Sensors:

         Stars will absorb thus nullify) both Klingon and Federation
    Phaser-Type  fire.  They will also absorb one photon torpedo, but can
    be destroyed by a second.  stars will also block Short-Range  sensors
    from  detecting  Klingon  positions.   The  positions of starbases or
    stars, however, due  to  their  fixed  natures,  will  be  filled  in
    automatically by the ship computer.

    Scoring And Rank:

         The computer scores every game you complete upon the  number  of
    stardates you used, the size of the galaxy and the number of Klingons
    you  killed.   Then  in  the  interest  of  energy  conservation,  it
    multiplies  this  number  by  a  factor  called  resource utilization
    factor, which is based upon the amount of energy  you  used  and  the
    number of photon torpedoes you fired per Klingon killed combined with
    the number of times you docked at a starbase  and  the  size  of  the
    galaxy.  This now becomes your rating for the battle with a rating of
    about 1000 being good.   This  number  is  then  combined  with  your
    running  total  which is used to determine your cumulative rating and
    rank.  The 12 ranks are; Yeoman, Ensign, Lieutenant  JG,  Lieutenant,
    LT  Commander,  Commander,  Captain,  Commodore,  Rear  Admiral, Vice
    Admiral, Admiral, and Fleet Admiral.  A new  player  is  assigned  an
    Ensign with a cumulative rating of 500.












